name: Joanna Letz
bio: Rooftop farm and floral design studio. Weekly deliveries / event design / u-picks. Educational offerings and private events at the farm. Berkeley, CA.

social_posts.post_text: Been quiet on here. Wanted to let you all know our dahlia tuber shop is open. Now’s the time to plan your summer garden- plant for abundance and beauty and for all the pollinators 🐝 🌸🌱💕

In addition to offering dahlia tubers this year we’re also offering V-Day flowers. Check out our shop for what we have. A reminder also that holidays can be an opportunity to love on yourself 💕💃. Whatever that means to you- maybe includes buying yourself some flowers 🌸 and supporting our farm.
null

✨Valentine’s Day ✨is coming up next week. Flowers are kinda a thing on Vday. And makes sense, the ephemeral beauty of nature as a way to express love. This is also your reminder to order now for yourself or a loved one. We’re taking orders thru Wednesday this week❤️. You can also get yourself or gift a flower club subscription and enjoy our flowers thru the season 💕🌸. And the newsletter just dropped- send a note if you want to receive it. Or sign up on our website. Newsletter includes hot tips on what we have planned for this year and musings on the shift in seasons and other notes/ poems from the rooftop.

Last day to order Valentines flowers from us 🌸💕. This is your reminder to not wait until the last minute. Send yourself or a loved one some delicious beauty and support our farm on the roof ✨. You can also give the gift that keeps giving by signing up for our flower club. If ya sign up this week we’ll deliver your first flowers on Vday and we’ll add in an extra posy 💐.

We’re taking some more Vday orders ❤️So if ya haven’t gotten em in now’s the time. Also looking forward to these crops coming on the scene soon. Lots of flowers to get excited about. You can also sign up for our flower club (weekly, bi weekly and monthly subscriptions)! Headed into year 9 of Bluma Farm! Hoping this will be the year the flowers sell themselves 🌸 and we have lots of fun parties to celebrate the bounty and gatherings to support the urban ag community!
Harvesting delicious geranium for our Valentines 💕 bouquets. We’ve extended our ordering - we got lots of flowers for you 💃
Harvesting a few more things for our bouquets. We got a few left for Valentines Day 💕. Order on our shop ✨✨
Making pretty things and harvesting delicious jasmine 💕✨

✨Dahlia tuber shop is open ✨ we’ll be starting to dig em up and ship next week. Get your orders in asap if ya want some of these beauties to plant in your garden or farm 🌱🌸 . Also sending out a newsletter today if ya wanna hear about what’s going on at the farm and other seasonal musings and thoughts from yours truly-  subscribe on our website 💃.

Thank you @sunsetmag for including me in the most recent issue of the magazine. Check out the article online (link in profile) or pick up a copy at your local bookstore. @buildersbooksource in Berkeley has some. And thank you @sunsetphoto for coming out to the farm and capturing the magic. I'm excited to get going on this season and bring beauty and flowers to all of you and the pollinators too. We got some fun things in the works. One of them being our first ever Spring Party (and plant sale 🌱), Sunday April 30th mark your calendars. We're also excited to announce we'll be hosting private events and workshops at the farm. Get in touch if you have a party you're planning and want us to host you.

Bluma is for lovers! We were so happy to design a beautiful mandap for Lakshmi and Jaxon's wedding in their sweet San Geronimo family's home. We used harlequin marigolds, scabiosa and thornless raspberry organically grown on our Berkeley rooftop farm as well as dahlias, garden roses and tuberose for Lakshmi's bouquet.​​​​​​​​
.​​​​​​​​
.​​​​​​​​
.​​​​​​​​
#blumalovers#blumaweddings#bayareaweddings#berkeleyweddingflorist#bayareaweddingflorist#locallysourced#organicblooms

The tables at Lakshmi and Jaxon's wedding reception at Deer Park Villa were some of our favorites. The groom had a strong connection to flowers and plants through his former work as a landscaper. He asked that we block the colors and blooms so that the arrangements reflected the natural beauty of the blooms. It was a joy to execute his vision.​​​​​​​​​.
.
.
#blumalovers#blumaweddings#bayareaweddings#berkeleyweddingflorist#bayareaweddingflorist#locallysourced#organicbloom

Last summer, the Bluma team had a blast designing this mandap for a very special couple. Especially significant was the structure itself as it contained the history of the groom's family gatherings and many memorable events under it's boughs. It was a wonderful day full of love, laughter and celebration. Photo by @annawuphoto.​​​​​​​​

Exciting things happening in our basement studio. I would love a greenhouse but this works too 🌱🌱💕. Who’s coming to our Spring Party and plant sale? April 30th 1-4. We’ll have plants, drinks, a view, some flower crowns 🌸 👑, music!! Also newsletter is dropping today, send a note if you want to receive it :)

Harvesting some pretty anemones with our Berkeley High interns. And potting up tomatoes! I realized I’ve been away from the farm for a week and these blooms caught me by surprise ✨✨🌸. All that rain 🌧️, was that even this week? I guess the office work, being indoors, and managing the business side a things has me a bit dizzy. Nice to get back outside. Tmrw we’ll be planting with our Albany High interns. I’m also so excited for the things we’re planning this season! Come to our Spring Party and check out our last Sunday of the month floral series. 💗🌸🌸🌱

This week’s flower club bouquet!! Khalia modeling with our second bouquet of the season. The anemones are heartbreakers 💔. Join our 🌸 club. Modeled after vegetable CSA’s (community supported agriculture) we make you a hand wrapped bouquet each week with what’s blooming on the farm! You get to come along with us through the season and be an integral part of making this farm run. What better way to support a woman owned, urban farm! Our blooms are growing right here in the city of Berkeley. You can join for weekly, bi-monthly or a monthly subscription and if you need to skip a week cause you’re going outta town, you can start and stop at anytime 💕🌸. We can deliver to your door or you can pickup at our partner locations. Current pickup locations are at: @vbscwine on college, @oaktownspice on Grand, @hammerlingwines . We’ll likely be adding some new pickup spots soon. Also check the last photo ceanothus in full bloom on the roof ✨🐝

Happy Equniox and new moon 🌑 🌸🌱. Got some agrostema, digitalis and stock planted yesterday! Nice to plant on the Equniox. And got some apple tree pruning done. Hope y’all got to celebrate in some way. Today I’ll write a poem. Did you know it’s world poetry day? So write yourself or the Equniox a poem 💕. And then also sign up for our flower club and get yourself some flowers ✨✨

Hope everyone stayed safe in that crazy storm yesterday. Also on here to remind you to order your dahlia tubers. We’ll also have some available at our Spring Party and Plant Sale April 30th - get your tickets. Link in bio for tix and tubers. Happy Spring, lets go! Photos by Nicola Parisi.
Hello Monday. Thinking about all the harvesting we’ll be doing this summer. Sowing sunflowers 🌻 that will be in bloom in a couple months and same I hope for the agrostema aka Corncockle ✨.

Yesterdays harvest before the rain 🌧️. This morn I’m inside tackling office work. The constant flow of spreadsheets, to do lists and emails. Trying to strategize on tackling sales and marketing, budget planning, client communications,  website development, and then also making sure the farm is running smoothly too. I find most of it fun, and the challenge of putting all the pieces together excites me. I also know I can’t do everything. Today I’m meeting with my bestie and business advisor Lily to assess how to better prioritize and get this season off and running. If you’re looking for a way to support Bluma check out our offerings on our website ✨🌸. Thx for following along. And if you’re like me and try to do it all maybe take a step back and see where you could do things differently/ ask for help or delegate.

Get yourself out to the hills or a little spot with green and enjoy the sound of the frogs at night and the sweet smell of wet earth. This morning is clear and crisp. We’ll be planting our dahlias on the rooftop. This evening I’ll go back here and sit amongst the flowering lupine and look for mushrooms. Grateful to our wedding clients who also happen to choose colors that are in bloom in the hills. Give me all the silvery greys and purples in spring.

On an ideal summer day in Napa, these two lovebirds came up from LA to get hitched. We were so happy to bring our gorgeous organic rooftop blooms to add to their shine. With the  incredible @small.blue.planet and stunning photos by @paigegreenphoto.​​​​​​​​​.

Happy Monday! Currently indoors setting my mind to a long to do list. And looking thru spring arrangements from past years. Here’s a few. If you’d like to get your hands on some of our blooms and designs join our flower club. Weekly seasonal florals from our farm, delivered to your door or for pick up. Sign up - link in profile ✨✨🌸

Bachelor buttons growing with marigold gems. We’ll be planting these soon ✨. Not quite sure if it’s worth it to grow the bachelors but I love the bright blue color and edible flowers. Grow what ya love ❤️ 🌱

The butterfly ranuncs! Time to harvest these and get our dahlia tubers in the ground. ✨✨🌱🌱. Welcome Spring, it’s go time. Hope y’all are ready for some beautiful flowers this season and other fun stuff we got planned.

Pink moon, spring holidays, plants are growing. Celebrate one another, the moon and the flowers. If you’d like some blooms from the rooftop to enjoy over the weekend, to guide and welcome your spring celebrations, or maybe just a gift to yourself - hit us up asap so we can make somn for you.
Happy Friday ✨✨

Good morning ☀️. Often flowers remind me of ice cream 🍦. Maybe this would be a turmeric citrus ice cream. Looks like we’ll have an abundance of flowers this week. Florists if ya need some. And we’d love for more people to join our flower club. We’ll be offering a promotion this week (more info to come). Despite my best efforts I haven’t left the house yet today. Working on the back office stuff. Making sure I know what needs to get done this week so I can communicate the priorities to the crew. Headed to the farm soon to plant 🌱, phlox, cosmos, violas… 🌸🌸 and then harvest ranuncs!

Ooee. A bit of warm weather and we got some butterfly 🦋 ranunculus. And the tecolote ranuncs I think are my fav. The one on the cover would be a cinnamon and tangerine ice cream flavor. Sign up for our flower club this week and get an extra bouquet of these beauties ✨✨🌸🦋. Pickup and delivery available. Pickups @vbscwine @oaktownspice @hammerlingwines and we’re gonna add an SF spot too.

✨✨Flower club promotion ✨✨ join our flower club this week or next and get an extra bouquet of 🦋 ranunculus. Plus a gift certificate to either @hammerlingwines @vbscwine or @oaktownspice . If you refer a friend to our club we’ll send you a free bouquet or a bluma T-shirt!! 💕🌸🌱🌈

✨Flower club bouquet and bluma T-shirt giveaway✨ to enter: 1. follow @blumafarm, 2. like and save this post. 3. tag 2 friends in the comments (unlimited entries). Share this post to your stories for an additional 5 entries :) We’ll choose a winner next Wednesday 4/19. 🌈🌸 if you’re not local we can send you the shirt and you can gift someone else your bouquet.

Peak into a day in the life at Bluma farm. Not pictured, the quick lunch break thx to @berkeleybowl , hauling debris out of my van to make a compost pile at my house, computer time sending emails and organizing orders (from home on my kitchen floor lol), the fun visits and chats with friends and farmers, and then the moment I felt overwhelmed by all the things to do and flowers to sell. Finished off the day on a high note planting more dahlias with our B High interns and @__jeffinsf

Friday photo shoot with our Albany High interns and Michelle. Trying out a new backdrop. Was kinda ridiculous wrangling a large piece of paper in the wind. But we made it work! We got flowers. We’re at the farm for another hour if ya want to come by and snag some blooms send a dm or give us a call. 🌸🌸

Erica and Matt trusted us to design warm sweet- strawberry-summer florals from the rooftop for their cool space wedding. We loved every bit of it! Photos from the talented @alisonyinphoto and excellent planning by @rileylovesluluweddings.​​​​​​​​​.
.

This is our first ever Spring party! We’re so excited to host and celebrate spring!! 🌱🌸💐

Happy Tuesday ✨ we’re  prepping for our event this Sunday 4/30. Drop a note if ya plan to come through. 1-4pm at the rooftop. Music by @palm_fire @chelsea_blake_music @gregorygriffinmusic . Drinks and activities to be had and farm tours led by me. Plants, flower crowns and bouquets for sale 🌸 too.

The week of ranunculus blooms. They’re kinda unreal. Lots to do on the farm ✨. And we’re exited to host our Spring party on Sunday. Hope you can make it. And while you’re here you can also snag some of these beauties while your relaxing and sipping on drinks and listening to music and seeing what we’re up to.

Come join us at the rooftop tmrw for our spring party! We’ll have farm tours, a plant sale, music, kids activities, and drinks, 1-4pm. And you can get your hands on some a these blooms. We’ll have sandwiches for sale from Nomad Cafe as well.
Party time!!! Come hang with us today. 1-4pm. Music, drinks, food, farm tours, good people! I know the @warriors game is on. But hoping y’all can record and watch later ;)

Thank you to everyone who came out yesterday. What a wonderful party. So sweet to have so many people here who are excited about what we’re doing. What a great way to enter this next season. Thank you thank you!!! And so grateful for the Bluma crew and the talented and awesome musicians! Today marks the half way point between Spring and summer. A good time to celebrate. Lots to do over here on the rooftops. The pause before summertime feels important and to get to do that in community! To honor the shift in seasons, the flowers, the ecosystem, and the people that make it happen and who show up to party!

We're offering a discount if ya order today. Use code- MOMSDAY23 . We've also extended our promotion of our flower club. For the club (first bouquet is 50% off) use code, FLOWERCLUB!! Just sent out our newsletter. Includes “notes from the rooftop”, my musings about things happening on the farm. Also reminder order for your Mamas/ the Mamas in your life. We got some sweet gift collections for you and plant starter kits 🌱🌸💃. Order by Friday to get a discount. Code is MOMSDAY23

Kitchen sink flowers, cause this is the best photo I got right now. I’m excited we get to use these blooms in our Moms day bouquets this week. If ya order on our shop by tmrw morn you can use the discount code ✨MOMSDAY23✨

Good morning! Sweet to get some more showers this week 🌧️. It’s not always smiles over here, but when we’re harvesting beautiful things it’s hard not to :) . I sent out a newsletter yesterday and included a poem by Mary Oliver. See below ⬇️. I’m hoping to start a practice with the Bluma crew of beginning our week with an excerpt from a book or a poem. If we make this a continued thing, I’ll share those here as well. The ranuncs are almost done but I’m excited we have them for moms day this year. Also order by today if ya want blooms for the Mamas. Here’s the poem by Mary Oliver: Wild Geese, 
You do not have to be good.
You do not have to walk on your knees
for a hundred miles through the desert repenting.
You only have to let the soft animal of your body
love what it loves.
Tell me about despair, yours, and I will tell you mine.
Meanwhile the world goes on.
Meanwhile the sun and the clear pebbles of the rain
are moving across the landscapes,
over the prairies and the deep trees,
the mountains and the rivers.
Meanwhile the wild geese, high in the clean blue air,
are heading home again.
Whoever you are, no matter how lonely,
the world offers itself to your imagination,
calls to you like the wild geese, harsh and exciting -
over and over announcing your place
in the family of things.

Ooee we got some gorg blooms for the Mamas this week, from the rooftop 🌸. We’ll be taking orders thru today and if I can get all your last minute requests later in the week I will. But don’t wait pls 💕. Also partnering with @casadechocolates for a sweet gift collection 💐. Order on our shop.

Good morning ✨🌸. We’ll be delivering flowers to the Mamas today and Sunday. If ya want a bouquet or our gift bundle you can still order today for Sunday. Lots of beautiful blooms from the roof. Our gift bundle includes, flowers, our herbal tea mix, a bundle of lavender, and chocolate from @casadechocolates 🍫💐

Today was our Albany high interns last day. Khalia and Emily have been at the farm the last 2 seasons and now they’re bout to graduate! Each morning when they arrived we would chat about their AM math classes. I wish I could remember todays lesson! Today was also a busy one with getting flowers out to the Mamas. Thank you to our pinch hitters Michelle and Jeff! And Haia for making all the magic in the studio. Thank you to all who have ordered it means so much to us. You all are what makes us able to keep going and growing. We have a few more bouquets and gift bundles available for Sunday ✨✨ order on our shop. Im ready for a little rest and to watch the @warriors game and then we’ll be back on Sunday delivering flowers 🌸 🌸.

Harvesting some pretty fall planted violas ✨and campanula finally on the scene and the first of the godetia, taking its sweet time 🌸. Thank you all for your orders last week. Glad we could get blooms out to the mamas. As we step into our busy season we hope you’ll come along with us and sign up for our FLOWER CLUB. Our weekly, biweekly or monthly subscription offering. We’re gonna continue our promotion of the club for a bit longer so take advantage. Code is FLOWERCLUB!! For 50% off your first order. The club is a great way to support us and get our flowers. We’re still looking for an SF pick up spot if ya got one in mind. Our current east bay pick ups are @vbscwine on college and vine, @hammerlingwines and @oaktownspice on Grand. We also offer deliveries to your door 💕

Godetia she a pretty one. This morn I’ll be working on irrigation projects. Maybe one of my least favorite tasks. But it has to get done. And feeling a lot a things today. Sometimes I run aground when the biz side of things feels tough and at the same time I’m also needing a bit of space to tend to my personal life. And, here I am moving thru. Reminding myself what we’re doing: creating beauty and opening to the ephemeral nature of life, tending to plants, providing habitat. Today, I’m gonna work on letting the softness of the flowers and the cool air help me to stay in the present. Cause my minds capacity at the moment to try to figure everything out is running me in circles.

Made it off the farm and outta the bay for the weekend. Hung out with rad people and cool desert plants. Stared at the Milky Way, gathered around a fire, danced, felt the heat of the suns intensity, and the sweet shade of the cottonwood trees. Back on the farm, and the roof, and thinking about how we grow plants and create urban spaces. And the importance of letting our minds rest to gain new perspectives. Stepping into the summer season excited to continue growing things and hoping that the plants and the people will be excited too ✨.

Yesterdays cute bday delivery ✨✨🌸. We’re doing deliveries Tuesday- Friday in the east bay and some SF if you’re looking to send a sweet gift to someone, check out our online shop. I prolly need to hire someone to organize our shop better- but it’s there and you can order flowers from us! The flowers right now are too good. Godetia and campanula and sweet peas. Oh and gerber daisies. I almost got rid of the gerbers, but then was like they’re still alive, what the heck let’s put em in pots. And I think that’s the way to go with gerbers. Any growers out there got tips on those?

The chocolates are beginning. Did you know one of my favorite things about growing flowers are all the pollinators 🐝 I get to be around. The habitat we tend for them brings me great joy. Plant some 🌸 in a window box or yard or roof, and let some space go a little wild. My garden at home right now is quite the weedy wonderland. Second photo was my original attempt at a logo 8+ years ago :) and then a sketch of my grandma. Bluma means flower in Yiddish, my grandparents first language. Any yiddish speakers out there who want to teach me?
Campanula and godetia harvest on the roof 💃.

Matilla poppies in bloom again. Photos from @imnofiction ✨✨📸 . I love the visceral feeling of these film photos. Maybe it’s time to break out my old camera. I feel as tho I could shape shift into some dyers chamomile on an afternoon harvest the last day of May.

Agrostema about to be full on. ✨✨Today is warmer and I’m reminded it’s summertime and we’re gonna have an abundance of flowers. We’d love for more people to be part of our Flower club. And also wondering how else we might get our flowers out into the world/ serve the community. Any thoughts or other things you want to see us offering? Thx- Joanna 🌸

Recent life outtakes and sounds. Today felt like a hustle maybe this week too, and it’s only Tuesday. But the plants and water and quiet sounds are my current guide and reminder to slow down so maybe someone else is needing this too. And if ya can go find that quiet place out in the world or find a patch of weeds or flowers or a tree to sit next to 🌱💦.

Ode to the pincushion flower. You are a bounty of flowers. Bees land easily and enjoy your nectar and pollen grains. We harvest you as much as we can and still you produce more. A plethora of colors both vibrant, like the velvet purple, and muted like the Fata Morgana. Sugary clouds of pink and white I can imagine a dreamscape room filled with your likeness. I hope people will go home with armloads of your blooms grown on the rooftop so we can keep planting you and feeding the pollinators.

So many visitors this week!! 🐝🐝 I heard the hummingbird moths are seeing a boom in their population this year. I was very surprised to see one on the roof! And had just been talking about how I didn’t think they would fly six stories up. I often tell people one of my favorite things about growing flowers are all the pollinators I get to be around. Plant forage for the bees and insects! We need more habitat for them. And why not? They lift my spirits and I’m sure they will yours too. So much of what we are up to on the roof, growing things, are not seen and felt unless you come and visit! And so much of what we do is work we are not getting paid for. Farming is a public service!! Who can name all of insects seen here?
What a week!! August blooms. Tired farmers, beautiful flowers, beautiful people, more to come! Abundance, love, desire, being, dancing through it all 💃💃🌸🌸. Happy Friday, Shabbat shalom.

Last nights sunset. Heading into Monday with lots of feels. And many blooms to go out into the world. Thinking about how to hold the awe for the world amidst so much heartache. And the flowers, they ease our hearts in times of trouble and also times of joy. Flowers are good for the soul. We need them to feed ourselves and feed the world around us and all the insects and pollinators. I wish all of you could hang with me while I’m working and harvesting and experience what it’s like to grow things, and see the life that emerges from the flowers. I hope to organize another event soon. And life is full and carrying all the things is both beautiful and at times heavy. More to come. 🐝🐝🌻🌻💃🌸

Ooee week of the dahlias. August!!! So good, so many heartbreaks, so much feeling, so much doing. So many hours picking, hawking, talking, listening. And now taking a little break to lift some weights. Thx @baystrength !! From farming to working out. And I spend a lotta my time on the computer. Being a business owner means lm not always the one out in the flowers. I get to do that too. Usually while simultaneously doing other things. Also thank you @lovenfreshflowers @notillflowers for the tip on the blizzard dahlia. Also realized (while listening to Jenny talk about overwintering dahlias in Philly) we can easily leave our tubers on the roof over the winter and then dig em up when we’re ready to divide. We’ll be selling tubers again next spring! And we usually have a nice tuber harvest as we don’t have to compete with gophers.

Scenes from a Saturday harvest. Took a day off the farm to hang at the beach! Now back to picking. These cosmos look like someone painted the petals 🎨. Also did you know there’s a type of bee 🐝 that collects pollen on its abdomen and not it’s legs. Not sure who this bee is but it’s defs collecting pollen on its abdomen. So cool!

Harvest scenes. The morning light shifting toward fall. It’s hot and I can feel the nights getting longer. We got some beautiful blooms this week. Flowers are ephemeral. In a moment they’ll be gone. Our life is like that too. I lived for a time @sanfranciscozencenter and each morning someone would play the Han and call people to the mediation hall. On the instrument it says something like - “don’t waste this life!” So go enjoy the flowers and be kind and all the rest.
Today was a hot one and I’m a bit delirious. The bees are loving the jungle of love in a Puff vine and so am I. Plus clematis harvest off the roof.

Good morning! I’ve been away from the farm for almost a week! I’ll post some from my trip soon. In the meantime enjoy this accidental photo of me harvesting love in a puff vine. Trees and plants of Central Park. Left the farm for a week and got to explore parts of NYC. Creating space to let my mind wander and observe plants, people and my mind. I think we all need this, time to sit and listen. The dedication I have undertaken in farming is really a dedication to observation. My wish and hope is that we all can cultivate skills in observing and take time to create relationships with the plants around us and with the earth and ground we stand on. It’s an enriching and healing experience ❤️❤️🌱🌱🌱. And in turn also acknowledge the history of the land in which we find ourselves. And what it truly means to honor and give voice to that. In Berkeley, CA the rooftop farm sits on the territory of xučyun (Huichin), the ancestral and unceded land of the Chochenyo speaking Ohlone people.

First order of the week. I just want to melt in this bucket. So good. Like an ice cream sundae sprinkled with Silene. We’re harvesting it as a cut but it’s high time I tried some - maybe in todays lunch.
